cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.NE 

This paper deals with deep NLP models and their underlying structures, which are typically extracted using off-the-shelf parsers. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also proposes a novel approach for end-to-end learning of latent structure predictors, which involves machine learning techniques such as SparseMAP inference and dynamic computation graph construction. Hence, the paper could also be categorized under cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of parse trees, which are commonly used in computer vision tasks, suggesting that the paper could also be categorized under cs.CV (Computer Vision).
